text: Ralph Laurence See (born June 20, 1960 in Norwalk, California) is a former first baseman. He played in 26 games for the Los Angeles Dodgers and Texas Rangers during the 1986 and 1988 baseball seasons. ==Career== After leaving the Rangers organization in 1988, he played in the Mexican League through 1994 before attempting a comeback with the San Diego Padres. He played in the minors for the Padres in 1995, with the Rancho Cucamonga Quakes and Las Vegas Stars. He then managed the Arizona League Padres in 1996 and played in the Northern League for the Thunder Bay Whiskey Jacks and Duluth–Superior Dukes from 1997–1999.
